Kasinka Mała [kaˈɕinka ˈmawa] is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Mszana Dolna, within Limanowa County, Lesser Poland Voivodeship, in southern Poland. It lies approximately 7 kilometres (4 mi) north-west of Mszana Dolna, 29 km (18 mi) west of Limanowa, and 39 km (24 mi) south of the regional capital Kraków.It is inhabited mostly by Zagórzan Gorals.
The village has a population of 3,500.